{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Request to external API includes complete taxonomy labels.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module-to-client payload handoff (request builder -> API client). A unit test of only a formatter could miss wiring bugs where taxonomy is dropped before send. REAL-INFRA is not required: a stub transport that captures outbound payload is sufficient. Rejected higher levels: no need for real OS/network/subprocess; behavior text is only about request content, not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire classifier with a fake API client that records outbound requests. Invoke classify() with a taxonomy and assert the sent payload contains the full label set (no missing/extra labels) on every dispatch path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Unknown provider label maps to \"unknown\".","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is at response handoff boundary (API response parser/adapter -> normalization -> return value). A pure unit on normalization logic can miss envelope/parsing wiring errors. Real infra not needed; deterministic fake API response reproduces the failure. Rejected higher levels: text specifies membership check against taxonomy, not real model judgment quality.","test_description":"Use a fake API client that returns an out-of-taxonomy label (e.g., \"medical\"). Call classify() and assert returned label is exactly \"unknown\" and raw unexpected value is not forwarded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Normalization is deterministic for identical raw responses.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior is one local transformation: same raw input -> same normalized label. No module boundary, I/O, or external dependency is required. Rejected higher levels: behavior text explicitly scopes to \"identical raw API responses\" and \"normalization step,\" disqualifying infra/LLM needs.","test_description":"Call normalization function/object repeatedly with the exact same raw response fixture and taxonomy; assert identical output each time (including casing/whitespace variants when fixture is unchanged).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Repeated live calls for same input remain consistent unless provider response changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on live AI API behavior across repeated calls. A stub cannot expose provider nondeterminism or model-side drift; mocking would hide real failures. Not Workflow: this is a single classify step repeated, not a multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run N real classification calls for the same document+taxonomy, recording raw provider response and final label each time. Assert label changes only when raw provider response differs; flag instability where equivalent provider outputs produce different labels.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.73,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Token budget is enforced before dispatch (truncate/reject per policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is cross-module orchestration: budget config + tokenizer/counting + dispatch gate. A unit on token counter alone misses 'enforced before send' wiring bugs. Real network is unnecessary; fake client can verify whether dispatch was blocked/modified. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is pre-dispatch policy enforcement, not model output quality.","test_description":"Configure small budget and policy (truncate or reject), invoke classify() with oversized input, and assert behavior before send: either transformed request respects budget or call is rejected without dispatch. Verify fake client sees compliant payload or no call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for typical document stays within configured budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This requires real provider token accounting from a real AI API call; in-process fakes can always report compliant numbers and hide real overruns. Per LLM-DEP rule, execution through real AI API with assertions depending on provider-returned model metadata remains Agentic. Not Workflow: single call metric check.","test_description":"Execute real classify() calls on representative documents with configured budget, capture provider-reported token usage from responses, and assert usage <= budget for each case; fail on any over-budget report.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"On rate-limit signal, module waits and retries instead of returning error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is retry orchestration across modules (error classifier, backoff policy, retry loop, client). A deterministic fake API can emit rate-limit then success to expose logic bugs; real network is not strictly required for minimum failure detection. Rejected higher levels: behavior text targets transport error handling, not model output content or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Use fake API client scripted to return rate-limit response first, success second; use controllable clock/sleeper. Assert classify() does not fail immediately, performs wait/backoff, retries expected number of times, and returns successful label.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
